Initial settings: Add a User, Network Settings, Configure Services, display the list of services which are running, 
                  Stop and turn OFF auto-start setting for a service if you donâ€™t need it, Sudo Settings.
                  
1. Adding a user:
  adduser <username>

2. iP Address
   sudo ifconfig -a

3. To run, start, enable service
  sudo systemctl [command] [service_name]

4. To stop and restart the service in Linux, use the command:
  sudo systemctl restart SERVICE_NAME
  sudo systemctl stop SERVICE_NAME

5. List running services
  sudo systemctl -t=service --state=running

6. Sudo settings (when installing package)
  sudo apt install package-name
    
